The paper focuses on fine-grained image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves designing an end-to-end network and using saliency-guided localization learning, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its approach on a widely-used dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
